2039	[\(R_x\)-linear stalk--tensor comparison map (d.2, stage (iii))]
2040	  \label{lem:stalk_tensor_linear_map}
2041	  \lean{PresheafOfModules.stalkTensorLinearMap}
2042	  \uses{def:scheme_modules_tensorobj, lem:stalk_tensor_desc_forward, lem:stalk_linear_map}
2043	  With \(R\), \(A\), \(B\), \(x\) as in \cref{lem:stalk_tensor_commutation}, the
2044	  additive forward map \(\mathtt{stalkTensorDesc}\) of
2045	  \cref{lem:stalk_tensor_desc_forward} upgrades to an \(R.\mathtt{stalk}\,x\)-\emph{linear}
2046	  map
2047	  \[
2048	    \mathtt{stalkTensorLinearMap} \;\colon\;
2049	      (A \otimes^{p} B).\mathtt{stalk}\,x \;\longrightarrow_{R.\mathtt{stalk}\,x}\;
2050	      A.\mathtt{stalk}\,x \;\otimes_{R.\mathtt{stalk}\,x}\; B.\mathtt{stalk}\,x,
2051	  \]
2052	  agreeing with \(\mathtt{stalkTensorDesc}\) on underlying additive maps, and hence
2053	  still characterised on germs of simple tensors by
2054	  \[
2055	    \mathtt{stalkTensorLinearMap}\bigl(\mathrm{germ}_x(a \otimes b)\bigr)
2056	      \;=\; \mathrm{germ}_x a \,\otimes\, \mathrm{germ}_x b .
2057	  \]
2058	  This is the stage-(iii) landing of the construction narrated in
2059	  \cref{lem:stalk_tensor_commutation}, and the direct input to stage (iv) (the reverse
2060	  map).
2061	\end{lemma}
