2066	[Unconditional left-whiskering of the localizer, via d.2]
2067	  \label{lem:islocallyinjective_whiskerleft_via_stalk}
2068	  \lean{PresheafOfModules.isLocallyInjective_whiskerLeft_of_W}
2069	  \uses{def:scheme_modules_tensorobj, lem:stalk_tensor_commutation, lem:stalk_linear_map}
2070	  Let \(R\), \(J\) be as above with \(J.\mathtt{WEqualsLocallyBijective}\,\mathtt{Ab}\),
2071	  let \(F\) be an \emph{arbitrary} presheaf of \(R\)-modules, and let \(g : M \to N\)
2072	  be a morphism whose underlying morphism lies in \(J.W\). Then the left-whiskered
2073	  morphism \(F \triangleleft g = \mathrm{id}_F \otimes g\) is \(J\)-locally injective
2074	  (indeed lies in \(J.W\)). No flatness and no local-triviality hypothesis on \(F\) is
2075	  required. This discharges the open left-whiskering obligation
